  "doc_id": "21763",
  "text": "The induction coils radiate heat perpendicular to the coil axis. This could damage the system and decrease the thermal efficiency. Therefore, the electrical wires surrounding the nozzle are kept cool by using water jacket around them [CITATION_1] . The water jacket is further wrapped by insulating pads or husks to reduce thermal emissions outside the nozzle. Further the heat absorbed by this water jacket can be used to conserve energy by transforming it into other useful forms of energy.",
  "correct_citation": {
